INUMBER 1267
NAME 713
SUBSTANCE SOFTMETAL
PORTAL_CLIMB
WEIGHT 1000
HIDDEN
VOLUME 15
VARIABLE ZGUTCLP
VARIABLE ZGUTCLN
CONTAINER IN
INTERIOR 6
IFPREVERB GO -1
 IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 3
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You climb down into the gutter.
  ECHO OTHERS %n climbs down into the gutter.
  DISBAND
  MOVE ITEMVAL2
  AFFECT ITEMVAL2
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER The gutter is too small to climb into.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CLIMB -1
 IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 0     ; ** Going up
  IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 1    ; ** Thief only
   IFVAR ORG ! 13
    ECHO PLAYER The gutter looks ready to fall away from the building without your weight. Better think again.
    CLEARVERB
   ELSE
    IFVAR SKILL5 > 0
     RANDOM ZGUTCLP 1 100 0
     IFVAR ZGUTCLP ! 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You easily find firm hand and footholds and scale the gutter to the rooftop.
      ECHO OTHERS %n easily scrambles up the gutter to the rooftop.
      MOVE ITEMVAL2
      AFFECT ITEMVAL2
       ECHO OTHERS %n arrives after climbing up a gutter.
     ELSE
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER Halfway up, one of your handholds comes loose. You pinwheel your arms in midair and fall back down!
      POSITION LAY
      ECHO OTHERS Halfway up, %n suddenly falls away from the wall and slams back into the ground beside you.
     ENDIF
    ELSE
     RANDOM ZGUTCLN 1 2 0
      IFVAR ZGUTCLN = 1
       CLEARVERB
       ECHO PLAYER You think you're doing alright until three quarters of the way up, you judge a foothold incorrectly and plummet back down to the ground!
       POSITION LAY
       DAMAGEPLR CRUSH 10 Your head meets the ground in a not-so-surprisingly uncomfortable manner.
       ECHO OTHERS Judging a foothold incorrectly, %n falls away from the wall and slams into the ground with a pained groan.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR ZGUTCLN = 2
       CLEARVERB
       ECHO PLAYER As the gutter begins to protest bearing your weight with a loud groan, a burst of adrenaline allows you to scramble over the roof's edge.
       ECHO OTHERS As %n scales the gutter, it protests with a loud groan. Luckily %h makes it to the top intact.
       MOVE ITEMVAL2
       AFFECT ITEMVAL2
       ECHO OTHERS %n arrives after climbing a gutter.
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 0        ; ** general entry
   IFVAR SKILL5 > 0
   RANDOM ZGUTCLP 1 100 0
    IFVAR ZGUTCLP ! 1
     CLEARVERB
     ECHO PLAYER You easily find firm hand and footholds and scale the gutter to the rooftop.
     ECHO OTHERS %n easily scrambles up the gutter to the rooftop.
     MOVE ITEMVAL2
     AFFECT ITEMVAL2
      ECHO OTHERS %n arrives after climbing up a gutter.
    ELSE
     ECHO PLAYER Halfway up, one of your handholds comes loose. You pinwheel your arms in midair and fall back down!
     POSITION LAY
     ECHO OTHERS Halfway up, %n suddenly falls away from the wall and slams back into the ground beside you.
    ENDIF
   ELSE
    RANDOM ZGUTCLN 1 2 0
     IFVAR ZGUTCLN = 1
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You think you're doing alright until three quarters of the way up, you judge a foothold incorrectly and plummet back down to the ground!
      POSITION LAY
      DAMAGEPLR CRUSH 10 Your head meets the ground in a not-so-surprisingly uncomfortable manner.
      ECHO OTHERS Judging a foothold incorrectly, %n falls away from the wall and slams into the ground with a pained groan.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR ZGUTCLN = 2
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The gutter begins to protest your weight with a loud groan and you quickly make up your mind to get to the rooftop quickly. As luck would have it, you make it.
      ECHO OTHERS As %n scales the gutter, it protests with a loud groan. Luckily %h makes it to the top intact.
      MOVE ITEMVAL2
      AFFECT ITEMVAL2
      ECHO OTHERS %n arrives after climbing a gutter.
     ENDIF
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
 IFVAR ITEMVAL5 = 1         ; *** Going down
  IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 1        ; *** Thief only
   IFVAR ORG ! 13
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER The gutter looks ready to fall away from the building without your weight. Better think again.
   ELSE
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You carefully slide down the gutter.
    MOVE ITEMVAL2
    ECHO OTHERS %n carefully slides down the gutter.
    AFFECT ITEMVAL2
    ECHO OTHERS %n slides down a gutter and drops to %h feet beside you.
   ENDIF
  ENDIF
  IFVAR ITEMVAL1 = 0        ; ** General entry
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You carefully slide down the gutter.
   MOVE ITEMVAL2
   ECHO OTHERS %n carefully slides down the gutter.
   AFFECT ITEMVAL2
   ECHO OTHERS %n slides down a gutter and drops to %h feet beside you.
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB LOOK -1
 IFVAR INTNUM3 = 1
  ECHO PLAYER *** This item was scripted for the alleys but can be used wherever applicable. It involves a climbing skillcheck. Let ITEMVAL2 = destination room.
  ECHO PLAYER *** Let ITEMVAL5 = 1 if going down, 0 if going up. Let ITEMVAL1 = 1 if only thieves can use it, 0 if anyone can use it.
  ECHO PLAYER *** And just for you, Chris, let ITEMVAL1 = 3 for horizontal gutters that can be climbed into.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
