NUMBER 410
NAME Alley Home
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
You squeeze into the alley, brushing up against a pile of splintering crates.
You contort your face into an expression of utter disgust as your nose is 
barraged with the overwhelming stench of offal and human sweat. A steady drip
of water falls from a rooftop above your head, landing in an algae-infested
puddle at your feet.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT N 3524
ITEM 0 1040
 EXTEND 0 of wooden crates stacked into a crude shelter
ITEM 1 1563
 EXTEND 1 of foul-smelling algae
IFENTRY
 PLREVENT 2
 CONTPLREVENT
 ECHO ALL A rotten-toothed urchin peeks out of a home constructed of splintering crates with hate burning in his eyes, screaming, "My home! Leave Willigar 'lone!"
ENDIF
IFSAY WILLIGAR?
 PLREVENT 1
 CONTPLREVENT
 ECHO ALL Willigar's head appears through the entrance to his home and he barks, "Willigar's home. I'm Willigar!" He then rolls his eyes and disappears again into his crate.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH 0
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER The pile rocks back and forth precariously. You hear a shriek come from inside the pile.
 ECHO OTHERS You hear a shriek come from inside Willigar's home as %n shoves on it.
ENDIF
IFTOUCH 1
 CLEARVERB
 IFVAR INTNUM3 = 186
  ECHO GROUP %N reaches down through the mucky puddle and you immediately feel yourself pulled towards the muck. Your vision goes black for a moment and when it returns, you find yourself beneath the ground.
  MOVEGROUP 6304
  AFFECT 6304
  ECHO OTHERS A misty form oozes from the mucky grate above and solidifies into %n.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER You reach down and poke your finger through the surface of the puddle. Beneath, you feel an iron grate that feels much colder than it should be.
  ECHO OTHERS %N reaches down and pokes %h finger through the surface of the puddle of muck.
ENDIF
