NUMBER 413
NAME Mugger Lane
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Shadows crowd this narrow dead-end alleyway, most likely concealing any number
of unwelcome surprises. A small group of grimy-faced teenagers stand in a 
semi-circle around the base of a rusty iron rung ladder that climbs up the side
of the southern wall of the alley.
*DESCRIPTION_END
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT NW 412
EXIT E 817
ITEM 0 335 adj1=272 adj2=169 val2=416
IFPREVERB E -1
 IFVAR ORG ! 13
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER A knife hurtles through the air and imbeds itself only inches in front of your nose as you turn to head east. You look back to see the gangmembers all holding throwing knives. You take the hint that they don't want you leaving that way.
  ECHO OTHERS With a "whup-whup-whup" noise, a knife hurtles through the air and imbeds itself in a wall only inches in front of %n's nose.
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER Following the southern wall of the arena, the alley gradually turns to the northeast and opens into another alley.
  ECHO OTHERS %N follows along the southern wall of the arena and disappears from sight.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER The group of young men refuse to budge.%cOne of them looks up and growls, "Go away, stranger. You don't belong here."
 ECHO OTHERS The group of young men refuse to step aside from the ladder's base.%cOne of them looks up at %n and growls, "Go away stranger. You don't belong here."
 EQUAL FLAG3 1
ENDIF
IFSAY IT'S_OK,_FRIEND.
 IFVAR FLAG3 = 1
  IFVAR ORG = 13
   ECHO ALL With a slight nod, the leader of the gang steps aside, granting your group passage up the ladder.
   MOVEGROUP 416
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

