NUMBER 833
NAME Under the Fountain
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The cramped and dark passage from the north opens up at this point, into a
well-crafted stone chamber. A massive stone arch signifies the beginning of
the central sewer system, which follows Main Street west for the length of
Fayd. Through gutter drains above, you can make out many strange noises and
lots of people milling about the Bazaar. Some strange metal boxes are stacked
in the corner of the chamber, glistening with moisture and making a soft
humming noise of its own.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_GROUND
FIXED_LIGHT
EXIT N 895
EXIT W 846
; a storm grate (which views Bazaar Center (#206))
ITEM 0 883 adj1=1057
IFPREVERB EXAMINE 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You peer through the grate...
  ECHO OTHERS %N stretches a little to peer through the grate.
  SHOWROOM 206
  AFFECT 206
  ECHO ALL you notice a flicker of movement in the storm drain.
  AFFECT 833
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR RAC = 8
    DISBAND
    ECHO PLAYER Your ethereal form flows right through the bars of the grate.
    ECHO OTHERS %N's ethereal form flows through a grate in the ceiling.
    MOVE 206
    AFFECT 206
    ECHO OTHERS %N's ethereal form flows out from a nearby drainage grate.
  ELSE
    IFVAR MISTFORM = 1
      DISBAND
      ECHO PLAYER You urge your misty form upwards and through the bars of the grate.
      ECHO OTHERS A mist disappears through a grate in the ceiling.
      MOVE 206
      AFFECT 206
      ECHO OTHERS A mist seeps out from a nearby drainage grate.
    ELSE
      IFVAR SLIMEFORM = 1
        ECHO PLAYER You cannot reach the grate in the ceiling.
      ELSE
        ECHO PLAYER You would never fit, and the grate is firmly attached.
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
; a strange metal box
ITEM 1 378 adj1=1038 adj2=192
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
This strange contraption has several conduits connected to the side, and a
thick pipe which leads to an oily tank next to the box. You think that only
the Technologists could have dreamed this thing up.  What it does exactly
isn't obvious from where you're standing.
*DESCRIPTION_END
; an oily metal tank making a humming noise
ITEM 2 847 adj1=221 adj2=192
 EXTEND 2 making a humming noise
IFPREVERB KICK 2
  IFVAR ROUNDTIME = 0
    CLEARVERB
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 10
    ECHO PLAYER You kick the tank, and it stops humming.%cJust as you think you have broken it, it starts up again.
    ECHO OTHERS %N kicks an oily metal tank, and it stops humming for a moment.
    AFFECT 206
    ECHO OTHERS The fountain water shuts off abruptly.%cJust as quickly, it resumes a moment later.
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You kick an oily metal tank making a humming noise!
    ECHO OTHERS %N kicks an oily metal tank making a humming noise!
  ENDIF
ENDIF
