; from gate844 to bog845 (out of fayd)
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The main passage of this pipe is narrower to the west, and wider to the east.
To continue eastward, you must find a way through a slimy grill of metal bars
set into the stone arch.  The water is rushing between the bars into this clay
and stone passage.  As it nears the river, a few smaller ducts and channels
split away from the main raging flow of scum, and divert it to several unknown
locations.  You're not sure if that's to reduce the terrible effect it has on
the river, or to make it harder to bring large armies of attackers through the
narrow mouth of the sewers.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_GROUND
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
