out a larger chamber south of this point.  As the cavern widens, the stream
of dirty water grows; several inlets in the walls trickle rainwater from Grand
Avenue, above.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_GROUND
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
EXIT N 893
EXIT S 833
; a storm drain (peeks to street (#261))
ITEM 0 1101 adj1=1057
IFPREVERB LOOK 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You peer through the storm drain...
  ECHO OTHERS %N gazes up through a storm drain.
  SHOWROOM 261
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The opening is too small.
ENDIF
; some grafitti
ITEM 1 235
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
The grafitti isn't the usual set of slurs you've found elsewhere.  Instead of
rude jokes about murgs, and naughty aelf poetry, you see a series of rough but
detailed diagrams.  Box shapes and lines and arrows are arranged carefully
all along the dry walls of the passage.  Some words are faded to be mostly
illegible.  'X' marks punctuate some of the diagrams.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB RECALL 1
  ECHO PLAYER It appears to be a map of some of the nicer homes around Tilvaen and Thinvar.
  IFVAR SKILL32 >= 2
    ECHO PLAYER You seem to remember there was a series of nasty robberies a few years back; these may be some of the thieves' notes on which houses to rob.
    IFVAR SKILL32 >= 8
      ECHO PLAYER Right about that time, there was a big political discussion as to whether or not there was a "Thieves' Guild," or whether the thieves worked individually.
      IFVAR SKILL32 >= 20
        ECHO PLAYER It was 1025, the year before Mugger Bob's Emporium was destroyed in a suspicious explosion, if you recall correctly.
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
