ITEM 8 198 adj1=1094
;
;
NUMBER 945
NAME Mullock Heaps
; from bway229
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
Beyond a row of wooden bins, several enormous heaps of trash and discarded
items loom to the tops of the buildings of the Poor Quarter.  Several human
and murg laborers are using pitchforks to sort through the refuse.  Those
items which can burn are being pushed down into a shallow depression; a thick
plume of black smoke rises from a sooty bonfire constantly being stoked and
tended.  An apprentice mage is sitting in one corner, picking out several
orbs and wands that have been discarded around town.
*DESCRIPTION_END
OUTDOOR_OTHER
FIXED_LIGHT
EXIT NW 229
; an enormous pile of burnable rubbish (container-on)
ITEM 0 1168 adj1=451
 EXTEND 0 of burnable rubbish
IFPREVERB LIGHT 0
  ECHO PLAYER Just as you are about to set a flame to the whole heap, a murg pokes you in the ribs.  "My job!"  He then hauls some of the rubble to the bonfire.
  ECHO OTHERS %N tries to start a bonfire on the enormous pile of burnable rubbish, but is stopped by a laboring murg.  "My job!" the murg protests.
ENDIF
; a huge pile of ruined metal and stone debris (container-in)
ITEM 1 1040 adj1=163
 EXTEND 1 of ruined metal and stone debris
; a great pile of rotting food, crawling with rats (portal)
ITEM 2 1040 adj1=457 val2=945
EXTEND 2 of rotting food, crawling with rats
;//TODO: change item 2 to archetype 610 (a portal 'pile')
;//TODO: point it to a poor quarter rooftop (school?) with val2
IFPREVERB GO 2
  ECHO PLAYER You hold your breath and try to climb the stinking refuse.
  ECHO OTHERS %N attempts to climb a great pile of rotting food, slipping and sliding the whole way.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB EAT 2
  ECHO PLAYER You can't find anything on the heap that would satisfy your tastes.
  ECHO OTHERS %N scrounges around the pile of rotting food.
ENDIF
